      "message": "The user is automatically created only with the user factory enabled. Otherwise, it tries to authenticate using the preconfigured username/password in the environment settings.\n\nThe implementation for API-based login and for the user factory are completely separate modules. They interact in this context but only interdirectly, because the login helper calls `api` which in turn gets the `user` to authenticate which in turn automatically provisions a user before returning its name.\n\nhttps://doc.wikimedia.org/rubygems/mediawiki-selenium/MediawikiSelenium/LoginHelper.html\nhttps://doc.wikimedia.org/rubygems/mediawiki-selenium/MediawikiSelenium/UserFactoryHelper.html\n\nHope that helps. :)",
